## Motivation/summary

<!--

change and rationale for the approach taken.
-->

We need geolocation information on mobile events in order to properly display location-related charts in Kibana's mobile dashboard.

These changes aim to add the client.geo* attrs to logs that contain the attr `client.ip`, which at the moment is only set to mobile-related logs.

issue.title: helm: create a Helm chart for apm-server binary
issue.body:
## Motivation/summary

WIP, experimental Helm chart for deploying APM Server standalone in Kubernetes, either as a Deployment+Service, or as a DaemonSet.

Each pod gets a volume for its data directory, defaulting to emptyDir but configurable through Helm values. The Helm chart generates a self-signed TLS certificate and a random secret token. The chart's values currently enable tail-based sampling by default for testing/demonstration purposes; this would be switched to disabled later.

## Checklist

- [ ] Update [CHANGELOG.asciidoc](https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/blob/main/CHANGELOG.asciidoc)
- [ ] Update [package changelog.yml](https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/blob/main/apmpackage/apm/changelog.yml) (only if changes to `apmpackage` have been made)
- [ ] Documentation has been updated

## How to test these changes

1. Clone the PR
2. Create an Elastic Cloud deployment (for Elasticsearch & Kibana)
4. `helm install <name> ./helm --set elasticsearch.host=https://....es.elastic-cloud.com:443 --set elasticsearch.username=elastic --set elasticsearch.password=<password>`

## Related issues

https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/issues/2107

pull_request.title: helm: create a Helm chart for apm-server binary
pull_request.body:
## Motivation/summary

WIP, experimental Helm chart for deploying APM Server standalone in Kubernetes, either as a Deployment+Service, or as a DaemonSet.

Each pod gets a volume for its data directory, defaulting to emptyDir but configurable through Helm values. The Helm chart generates a self-signed TLS certificate and a random secret token. The chart's values currently enable tail-based sampling by default for testing/demonstration purposes; this would be switched to disabled later.

## Checklist

- [ ] Update [CHANGELOG.asciidoc](https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/blob/main/CHANGELOG.asciidoc)
- [ ] Update [package changelog.yml](https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/blob/main/apmpackage/apm/changelog.yml) (only if changes to `apmpackage` have been made)
- [ ] Documentation has been updated

## How to test these changes

1. Clone the PR
2. Create an Elastic Cloud deployment (for Elasticsearch & Kibana)
4. `helm install <name> ./helm --set elasticsearch.host=https://....es.elastic-cloud.com:443 --set elasticsearch.username=elastic --set elasticsearch.password=<password>`

## Related issues

https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/issues/2107

pull_request.title: docs: Clean up OpenTelemetry docs
pull_request.body:
## Motivation/summary

Updates documentation related to OpenTelemetry based on issues found during our docs bug bash last week.

## Checklist

- [x] @colleenmcginnis update documentation:
  - [x] Remove most of the content in [Other execution environments](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/apm/guide/current/open-telemetry-other-env.html) page and rename to "AWS Lambda support" (https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/commit/1cca6cdec279106c413888ad764ee39fa79d82eb)
  - [x] Update links on the OpenTelemetry [Limitations](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/apm/guide/current/open-telemetry-known-limitations.html) page (https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/commit/8957ca5f5517ee5df68fc9e14c932474b4f602bc)
  - [x] Clarify that the code in [OpenTelemetry native support](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/apm/guide/current/open-telemetry-direct.html) is just a Java example (https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/commit/51287a1d43d581b2f01d75b857b9af1c3d220398)
  - [x] Remove the TSVB example in [Collect metrics](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/apm/guide/current/open-telemetry-collect-metrics.html) (https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/commit/ddf75de9d4e38b4c6948054c9e2066eab810ea40)
  - [x] Remove the resource attributes link in [OpenTelemetry native support](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/apm/guide/current/open-telemetry-direct.html) (https://github.com/elastic/apm-server/commit/0f201673e5cd90c41527496932207775e4c87707)
- [ ] @AlexanderWert review

## Related issues

* Closes https://github.com/elastic/observability-docs/issues/3291
* Closes https://github.com/elastic/observability-docs/issues/2196
